  "prompt": "Can you make a living setting up and running a charity?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to make a living by working for a charity, particularly in leadership or executive roles. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Salary Potential\n- Executive directors can earn $50,000-$150,000+ annually\n- Senior management positions typically pay well\n- Salaries depend on organization size, funding, and mission\n\n2. Job Roles\n- Executive Director\n- Development/Fundraising Director\n- Program Manager\n- Grant Writer\n- Financial Administrator\n- Marketing/Communications Specialist\n\n3. Considerations\n- Salaries are generally lower than equivalent corporate positions\n- Some view charity work as a mission-driven career\n- Requires strong management, fundraising, and organizational skills\n- Nonprofit experience and advanced degrees can increase earning potential\n\n4. Funding Sources\n- Government grants\n- Private donations\n- Corporate sponsorships\n- Fundraising events\n- Endowments\n- Membership fees\n\n5. Legal Requirements\n- Must register as a non-profit organization\n- Comply with financial reporting and tax regulations\n- Maintain transparency about fund usage\n\nWhile possible to earn a living, success depends on effective management, networking, and demonstrating the charity's impact.",
